TYPHOID FEVER - TAJIKISTAN (02)
*******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon, 6 Sep 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Infectious and Parasitic Diseases News, 6 Sep 2004
[translated by Mod.NR; edited]
<http://www.infectology.ru/news/news/calendar.asp?date=09/06/04>

Epidemic of abdominal typhus in Tajikistan
------------------------------------------
An epidemic of abdominal typhus [typhoid fever - Mod.LL] continues in
Tajikistan. The cause of the outbreak is leakage from the sewage
system.
According to sanitary epidemiological surveillance center chief
Davron Pirov, about 90 people are reported as infected in the north
of Tajikistan. According to him, the cause is a break in the sewage
system in the City of Pendjikent, 180 km north of Dushanbe. Waste
products leaked into the Zerafshan river, used for drinking water and
for field irrigation.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This report supplies a little more information regarding the
possible source of the water contamination. However, it is not clear
whether the cases reported are new since the previous post of 2 Sep
2004 -- see ref. below. - Mod.LL]
